ork or communication.\n**Main trade\u2011off**\nC offers the strongest combination of reliability, quick correct decisions, and a crew\u2011focused attitude, while his communication difficulty and egocentric tendency remain the primary concerns. The alternatives either lack comparable reliability (A, D) or exhibit far more severe interpersonal deficits (B).\n**Remaining uncertainty**\n- How severe is C\u2019s communication difficulty in practice? Could it lead to misunderstandings that affect safety?\n- Will C\u2019s egocentric attitude erode the positive crew atmosphere over long missions?\n- Does C possess adequate stress\u2011management abilities for sustained long\u2011haul pressure (no data available)?\n**What would change my vote**\n- Concrete evidence that C\u2019s communication problems or egocentric behavior cause operational or safety issues.\n- Information showing that A\u2019s \u201cunfriendly\u201d demeanor does not impede crew coordination and that he has proven stress\u2011handling capability.\n- Data indicating that B\u2019s interpersonal style is mitigated by strong teamwork practices, or that D has hidden crew\u2011resource\u2011management strengths.\nGiven the current balance of strengths and weaknesses, I continue to favor **Candidate\u202fC**, while acknowledging moderate uncertainty around his communication and stress\u2011handling profile.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
